      "level": 1,
      "text": "LaTeX"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "$\\KaTeX$ is used for rendering LaTeX math expressions. It can be enabled per page by setting <code>math</code> to <code>true</code> in the page front matter."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When enabled, the scripts, stylesheets and fonts from KaTeX will be included automatically in your site. You can start using LaTeX math expressions in your Markdown content."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Both inline and separate paragraph LaTeX math expressions are supported in the Markdown content."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Inline"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This $\\sigma(z) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}}$ is inline."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Separate Paragraph"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "will be rendered as:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Important"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Please enable and configure the passthrough extension in the Hugo configuration file. It preserves raw content within the delimiters to avoid rendering issues for complex expressions."
    },
